Blondell Reynolds Brown (born October 16, 1952) is an American politician and member of the Democratic Party. She is currently serving her fifth term as a member of Philadelphia City Council.
Reynolds Brown is one of two women, the other being Helen Gym, to win a Philadelphia At-Large Council seat since 1999.
On January 2, 2012 Reynolds Brown was elected the Council's Majority Whip, and is currently the only woman serving in City Council Leadership.
